        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:25:2",
        "text": [
          " حَدُّ الْجِوَارِ أَرْبَعُونَ دَاراً مِنْ كُلِّ جَانِبٍ مِنْ بَيْنِ يَدَيْهِ وَ مِنْ خَلْفِهِ وَ عَنْ يَمِينِهِ وَ عَنْ شِمَالِهِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "And from him, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Jameel Bin Darraj, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The limit of the neighbourhood is forty houses from every side, from in front of him, and from behind him, and from his right, and from his left’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. It is narrated from him (narrator of the Hadith above) from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Jamil ibn Darraj from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “The limits of a neighborhood are forty houses on all sides, front, back, right and left.” "
          ]
